---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionContainer from '../components/SectionContainer.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Health in the Spirit"
  description="How Health in the Spirit collects, stores, and uses information from visitors and newsletter subscribers."
>

  <SectionContainer variant="cream" padding="large">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-gold-700 font-semibold mb-4">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-forest-700 leading-tight">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-brown-500 italic">Last updated: June 15, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </SectionContainer>

  <SectionContainer variant="cream" padding="default">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <Prose>
        <p>This Privacy Policy explains what information Health in the Spirit collects, how we use it, and the choices you have. We keep it short and plain because we collect very little, and we never sell your data.</p>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>Health in the Spirit is a podcast and content website operated by Dr. Ryan DeNome and Annie DeNome in Ohio, United States. The site is built with Astro and Decap CMS and hosted on Cloudflare Pages. You can reach us about privacy at <a href="mailto:privacy@healthinthespirit.com">privacy@healthinthespirit.com</a>. The site address is <a href="https://healthinthespirit.com">https://healthinthespirit.com</a>.</p>

        <h2>What we collect, and why</h2>
        <p>We only collect what we need to run the site and respond to you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Newsletter email address.</strong> When you subscribe, we collect your email address (and your name, if you provide it) so we can send the updates you asked for. We store and send these through MailerLite, our email provider. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link at the bottom of any email.</li>
          <li><strong>Contact and guest-inquiry form details.</strong> When you use a form on the site, we collect the name, email address, and message you submit. These submissions are delivered to us through Web3Forms, a form-handling service, and then land in our email inbox so we can reply.</li>
          <li><strong>Direct email.</strong> When you email any of our published addresses, we keep that correspondence for as long as it stays useful to the conversation.</li>
          <li><strong>Basic server logs.</strong> Cloudflare, our host, automatically records standard request data (such as IP address, browser type, and pages requested) to keep the site online, fast, and secure. We use this only in aggregate for reliability and security.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising trackers, we do <strong>not</strong> run third-party analytics cookies, and we do <strong>not</strong> sell or rent your information to anyone.</p>

        <h2>Service providers</h2>
        <p>We share information only with the providers that help us operate, and only for that purpose:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>MailerLite</strong>: stores newsletter subscribers and sends our emails.</li>
          <li><strong>Web3Forms</strong>: delivers messages submitted through our contact and guest forms.</li>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong>: hosts and secures the website.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each of these providers handles your data under its own privacy terms. Because they operate in the United States and elsewhere, your information may be processed in the U.S.</p>

        <h2>Cookies and local storage</h2>
        <p>We use a small amount of browser storage for site preferences only, such as remembering that you have dismissed our top announcement bar. We do not use cookies to track you across other websites.</p>

        <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
        <p>You can unsubscribe from emails at any time, and you can ask us to access, correct, or delete the personal information we hold about you. Depending on where you live, you may have additional rights under laws such as the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) or the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). We honor these requests for everyone. Email <a href="mailto:privacy@healthinthespirit.com">privacy@healthinthespirit.com</a> and we will respond within a reasonable period.</p>

        <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>This site is intended for a general adult audience. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us information, email us and we will delete it.</p>

        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <p>We keep newsletter subscriptions until you unsubscribe or ask us to remove you, and we keep form messages and email correspondence for as long as they remain relevant to our conversation with you.</p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent change.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about privacy: <a href="mailto:privacy@healthinthespirit.com">privacy@healthinthespirit.com</a>.</p>
      </Prose>
    </div>
  </SectionContainer>

</BaseLayout>
